I see this allot in games/samples I am porting. The AudioManager of the NetRumble sample is a perfect example. It uses System.IO to enumerate a list of .xnb files which are in a directory. This allows dynamic content of sorts. I know there are other ways (a manifest file for example) but I though this might be a useful addition to the API. At the moment System.IO will NOT work on platforms like android so we end up with platform specific code to grab the "assets" from the Asset manager which is not ideal. when we could easily wrap this up into a useful helper method.

`string[] TitleContainer.GetFiles (string path);`

so we can use something like

`foreach(var sound in TitleContainer.GetFiles("audio") {
      soundsDictionary.Add(sound, Content.Load<SoundEffect>(sound));
}`

Thoughts?

When using native OpenTK (not SDL) on Mac. The GraphicsDevice Viewport is not updated correctly to reflect the screen resolution when in full screen mode. As a result it draw the game in the bottom right corner of the screen. This was working "something" changed to break this. 

